                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/4288</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SJH1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shea</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-29T17:00:00-04:42">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 29, 1916, 5 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.25 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your November 20, 4 p. m. Minister for Foreign Affairs submits the following
                    statement dated 28th:</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>In deference to the friendly request of the Government of the United States,
                        the Government of Chile, which has always zealously complied with the duties
                        imposed by neutrality, has no objection in declaring through the medium of
                        its Ministry for Foreign Affairs that the submarines in question are for the
                        use of Chile and will not be transferred to any of the belligerents during
                        present war.</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SJH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shea</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
